In the terminal window, navigate to your project folder and run the command npm init to initialize a new Node.js project.

Run the command npm install express mysql dotenv nodemon to install the necessary dependencies for your project.

mkdir migrations
touch create-orders-table.js
touch create-order-details-table.js
touch create-shippers-table.js
touch create-products-table.js
touch create-employees-table.js

// extra for fun
npm install spotify-web-api-node
npm install --save spotify-web-api-node

// important
create a .env file to store your sensitive information such as database connection string and API keys. Add .env to your .gitignore file to prevent it from being pushed to your GitHub repository.

//commit to repository
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push origin main

/* more controling options such as 
queryInterface object to drop the shippers table if it exists. You can use Sequelize's CLI tool to run the migration using the following command:

npx sequelize-cli db:migrate

This will execute the up function in the migration file and create the shippers table in the database. If you need to undo the migration, you can run the following command:

npx sequelize-cli db:migrate:undo

This will execute the down function and drop the shippers table from the database.
*/